Ah right, the seed complexity bites again.

@denmoroz There are essentially three things affecting randomness -- graph level seed, operation level seed, and operation current state. Setting seeds will guarantee the same pseudo-random sequence of numbers for an operation. If you want to generate a sequence of constants you need to recreate the operation for each number

This is simpler in numpy because np.random doesn't create operation with persistent state
